.TH OPROFILE 1 "@DATE@" "oprofile @VERSION@"
.UC 4
.SH NAME
oprofile \- a sytem-wide profiler
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B op_start
[
.I options
]
.br
.B op_stop
.br
.B oprofpp
[
.I options
]
[ sample-file ] [ binary ]
.br
.B op_help
[ event-name ]
.br
.SH DESCRIPTION
oprofile is a profiling system for Intel x86 systems running Linux 2.4. Profiling runs
transparently during the background, and profile data can be collected at any time. oprofile
makes use of the hardware performance counters provided on Intel P6 processors. See the HTML
documentation for further details.

